Title: Deve Herbes Pure Canola Oil 300ml -Brassica Napus 100% Natural Cold Pressed
Description: Benefits of Canola Oil:Lower Cholesterol: Canola oil contains absolutely no cholesterol, which is a major benefit for those people who have struggled with cholesterol issues in the past, as well as the conditions that naturally come with high cholesterol. It can actually reduce your cholesterol levels by 10-15%.Skin Health: Canola oil, is rich in vitamin E. Vitamin E is very effective as an antioxidant, and is able to protect the skin from the damaging effects of free radicals. This can keep your skin supple and smooth, increase the healing rate of injuries, reduce the appearance of blemishes and acne marks, and slow down the appearance of wrinkles.Cell Membranes: Vitamin E is also a lipid-soluble antioxidant, meaning that it can help protect the integrity of cell membranes throughout the body.Energy Levels: The low amount of cholesterol and the high amount of important antioxidants can help the body’s metabolism move at a normal rate. Your body doesn’t become sluggish and your energy isn’t sapped by slow circulation or an overstressed cardiovascular system.Brain Function: The antioxidants that combat free radicals also prevent damage to the brain, which can shut down neural connections and lead to diseases like Alzheimer and dementia.Diabetes: Monounsaturated fats not only help to prevent heart disease, but they can also help to maintain glucose levels in the blood.Using canola oil on eczema, dry heals, elbows and blemishes can effectively moisturize and soothe. Canola oil can also be used to treat dry, broken, frizzy hair and split ends. Hot oil treatments are often made with canola oil. It apparently also protects the hair from dirt, pollution and damage from the sun. Canola oil applied to the scalp can also help get rid of dandruff.
CategoryName: Health and Beauty>Bath and Spa>Body and Essential Oils

Title: Deve Herbes Pure Flax Seed Oil - Pack Of Two (100ml + 100ml) Linum Usitatissimum 100% Natural Cold Pressed
Description: Flaxseed is one of the most concentrated plant sources of omega-3 fats. Flaxseeds contain 50 to 60 per cent omega-3 fatty acids in the form of alpha linolenic acid. Flaxseeds are also rich in antioxidants, B vitamins, dietary fibre, a group of phytoestrogens called lignans, protein and potassiumFlaxseed oil is especially used to lower blood cholesterol and blood pressure. It improves kidney function, cures headaches associated with hypertension, rheumatoid arthritis and high cholesterol. It is also tried for treating osteoarthritis, anxiety, benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH), vaginal infections, dry eyes, “hardening of the arteries” (atherosclerosis), high blood pressure, heart disease, diabetes, and attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder (ADHD), constipation, for weight loss, and to prevent breast and prostate can.It soothes skin irritations & soften roughness. It is rich in fatty acids, vitamins and minerals & gives you healthy hair. Regular application of flaxseed oil promotes hair growth and prevents additional hair fall, eliminates dandruff and flakiness on the scalp, maintains the moisture content in the hair, keeping hair lustrous and healthy. Due to the high content of the omega 3 fatty acids, flaxseed oil reduces the level of LDL (good cholesterol) and maintains the HDL level in the blood.Flaxseed oil helps to reduce the pain and the inflammation in the joints of the knees caused due to arthritis, relieves pain, stiffness and improves mobility. Due to its anti-inflammatory properties, flaxseed oil can be used for the treatment of inflammatory bowel disorders like Crohn’s disease and colitisSome of us suffer from dry eye syndrome in which the outer layers of our eyes lack the required lubrication. This makes the eye sting and burn. A person suffering from dry eyes must take flaxseed oil to reduce the symptoms of dry eye syndrome.
